      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "#93041: fix(control-ui): restore Codex usage quota pill in sidebar session switcher",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThe Codex/OpenAI usage quota pill (shown in the Control UI chat that displays usage limits e.g. \"5h remaining\") was accidentally removed when the old chat header was replaced with a sidebar in PR #88772 (\"calm composer controls\").\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`ui/src/ui/chat/session-controls.ts` has a `sessionSwitcherOnly` flag. When true (as used by the new sidebar), both the model selector AND the quota pill were suppressed:\n\n```\nconst modelSelect = sessionSwitcherOnly ? \"\" : renderChatModelSelect(state);\nconst quotaPill = sessionSwitcherOnly ? \"\" : renderChatQuotaPill(state);\n```\n\nThe quota pill suppression was unintentional — only the model selector should be hidden in session-switcher mode. The quota data path (`fetchCodexUsage`, `collectQuotaWindowsFromAuthStatus`, `renderChatQuotaPill`) remains intact and functional.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### behavior\nRemove the `sessionSwitcherOnly` guard from the quota pill rendering so it appears in both the old header and the new sidebar.\n\n### environment\n- OS: Linux\n- Runtime: Node.js 22\n- Setup: OpenClaw main at 663fabbe30\n\n### steps\n1. Read the source file to confirm the old guard (`sessionSwitcherOnly ? \"\" : renderChatQuotaPill`) is replaced with unconditional `renderChatQuotaPill(state)`\n2. Run reproduction script to verify\n3. Run test suite\n\n### evidence\n\n**Source change verification:**\n```\nBefore: quotaPill = sessionSwitcherOnly ? \"\" : renderChatQuotaPill(state)\nAfter:  quotaPill = renderChatQuotaPill(state)\n```\n\n**Reproduction script output:**\n```\n=== Issue #93041: Codex Usage UI Verification ===\n\nFix applied: YES\nOld code present: NO (removed)\n\nrenderChatQuotaPill function exists: YES\nSidebar calls renderChatSessionSelect with sessionSwitcherOnly: YES\n\nConclusion:\n✅ The quota pill now renders even in the sidebar session switcher.\n✅ Fix: 1 line change (remove sessionSwitcherOnly guard on quotaPill).\n```\n\n**Test suite:**\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  104 passed (104)\n```\n\n### observedResult\n\nThe `renderChatQuotaPill(state)` call is no longer gated behind `sessionSwitcherOnly`. When the sidebar renders `renderChatSessionSelect(state, switchChatSession, { compact: collapsed, sessionSwitcherOnly: true, surface: \"sidebar\" })`, the quota pill is now included in the output.\n\n### notTested\nEnd-to-end visual rendering verification in a browser. The quota pill renders as a styled `<a>` element with `data-chat-provider-usage=\"true\"` attribute; its CSS grid placement is already handled by the `--has-quota` class modifier.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm test -- --run ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts` passes (104/104)\n- [x] Source diff confirms only the sessionSwitcherOnly guard is removed\n- [x] `renderChatQuotaPill` function and its data path remain unchanged\n- [x] CSS already handles the quota pill in the session-row grid via `--has-quota` class\n\n*AI-assisted: built with Claude Code*",
